	global.wikit1 = "Automatic Assault Rifle";
	global.wikit2 = "A standard assault rifle of Santa Claus's army, echoing the outline of the famous Kalashnikov rifle. It has moderate accuracy and effectiveness and is mainly used for burst fire. The rifle is designed to defeat enemy manpower, which reduces its effectiveness against protected targets. Developed long ago and gradually losing relevance, it has gone through many border conflicts and proved itself well. #Damage - 25 x 3";
	global.wikit3 = "Large-Caliber Bolt-Action Rifle";
	global.wikit4 = "Recently developed specifically to fight protected targets, this rifle shows moderate effectiveness against mechanized enemies. Armor-piercing bullets with a tungsten core penetrate up to 35 mm of steel, while having fairly modest behind-armor effect. Unfortunately, the weight and size of the design did not allow the rifle to be made automatic. Effective against well-protected targets, it performs more modestly against weak targets compared to the assault rifle. #Damage - 30 #Armor Piercing - 10";
	global.wikit5 = "Beam Rifle";
	global.wikit6 = "Our newest compact beam weapon, developed under Project X-MAS and using captured technologies of Eggman's Empire. The rifle's infrared beam ignores the target's armor and deals significant damage. Battery capacity allows the rifle to be used on the battlefield without reloading, while captured alloys help fight overheating effectively. Balancing captured technologies with Santa Claus's army tech level, the rifle suffers from high cost and more modest characteristics compared to enemy weapons. #Damage - 40";
	global.wikit7 = "Aircraft Cannon";
	global.wikit8 = "Designed specifically to fight armored targets, the aircraft cannon uses shells with a tungsten core and uranium jacket that penetrate a quarter meter of steel. The Gatling system reaches a rate of fire of 11,000 rounds per minute and can hit any known target suitable for interception.#Besides attacking air targets, it can also be used against ground targets, making it a universal weapon.#Range - 30";
	global.wikit9 = "Medkit";
	global.wikit10 = "Harsh Arctic conditions make surgery impossible in the field and complicate the use of standard field kits and medicines. The solution was special medicines, coagulants, and stimulants with an automatic blood-injection system. Timely injection can delay surgical intervention if needed and improve the wounded soldier's condition.";
	global.wikit11 = "Grenade";
	global.wikit12 = "A special high-power grenade used by Santa Claus's army. It can be used effectively against any targets. Powerful explosives and a special shell material allow it to ignore enemy armor within reasonable limits.#Good to demolish enemy buildings.";
	global.wikit13 = "AAM-SR ''Bullfinch''";
	global.wikit14 = "Short-Range Air-to-Air Missile ''Bullfinch'' is an advanced close-combat missile popular thanks to its small size and weight. It has a continuous-rod warhead and a heat-seeking guidance system, making it effective against most targets and allowing launches from distances greater than aircraft-cannon range. However, its IR seeker cannot retarget in flight, and the rod warhead, while able to instantly cut a target apart on a lucky hit, is ineffective against protected targets and cannot work against grouped targets. #Range - 60";
	global.wikit15 = "AAM-MR ''Stingray''";
	global.wikit16 = "An advanced Medium-Range Air-to-Air Missile with specially shielded systems. It combines semi-active and active radar guidance with a powerful high-explosive warhead. An excellent choice against most targets. Thanks to its active radar seeker, the missile can retarget in flight to the nearest target if the previous one was destroyed. In addition, the HE warhead allows it to work against grouped targets. #Range - 110";
	global.wikit17 = "AAM-LR ''Arrow''";
	global.wikit18 = "A deeply modernized Long-Range Air-to-Air R-33 missile using active and passive radar guidance systems. With a powerful shrapnel warhead, the missile accelerates to near-hypersonic speed in the final stage of flight, making its tungsten projectiles truly lethal. Unfortunately, the missile's heavy weight prevents hanging more than three missiles on a hardpoint. #Range - 200";
	global.wikit19 = "ASM ''Avalanche''";
	global.wikit20 = "A super-heavy Anti-Ship-class Missile developed specifically to fight the mothership of Eggman's air fleet. Its warhead is a 0.1 kt thermonuclear charge with a non-nuclear energy-beam detonator, allowing record system efficiency and acceptable reaction cleanliness compared to classic nuclear implosion. The missile's weight prevents hanging more than one missile on a hardpoint. #Range - 230";
	global.wikit21 = "Air Bomb";
	global.wikit22 = "Standard assault loadout of Santa Claus's aviation. Used to support ground forces from the air. Any aircraft can use it to destroy or weaken a target from above. Cheap and angry";
	global.wikit23 = "External Fuel Tank";
	global.wikit24 = "The standard external fuel tank (E.F.T) of Santa Claus's army. Used to increase aircraft flight range and is disposable. Use it if your fighters lack range, but keep in mind that it will be installed instead of a weapon.";
	global.wikit25 = "Lift";
	global.wikit26 = "An underground module with surface access, consisting of an armored cargo lift. Its load capacity and dimensions allow communication with the surface for both personnel and large objects (for example, aircraft) in disassembled form. #Vulnerable to bombing: yes";
	global.wikit27 = "Barracks";
	global.wikit28 = "A multi-story underground module designed for permanent base personnel residence and comfortable living. It has a recreation room, bathrooms (including showers), lockers for personal belongings, and sleeping bunks. Supports up to 30 people. #Vulnerable to bombing: no";
	global.wikit29 = "Laboratory";
	global.wikit30 = "An underground research module equipped with advanced scientific equipment for deep studies in chemistry, physics, and aerodynamics. Priority access is provided to Santa Claus army research centers, including experimental facilities (for example, wind tunnels). Supports 15 scientists. Lower floors study biological and mechanical beings under quarantine. #Vulnerable to bombing: no";
	global.wikit31 = "Workshop";
	global.wikit32 = "An underground engineering module equipped with the newest manufacturing equipment, including the latest tech centers and CNC machines. Allows production of almost all known parts and blanks. Supports up to 15 engineers. Assembly of especially large bodies of revolution is performed on automatic vertical turning lathes on lower floors. #Vulnerable to bombing: no";
	global.wikit33 = "Storage";
	global.wikit34 = "A utilitarian underground module that stores equipment, vehicles, and ammunition on different floors. For convenient transport, it is equipped with a cargo lift. #Vulnerable to bombing: no";
	global.wikit35 = "Hangar";
	global.wikit36 = "An underground module that stores up to two aircraft, services them, and launches them. Surface access is provided by a cargo lift that delivers the aircraft to a runway with an electromagnetic catapult. #Vulnerable to bombing: yes";
	global.wikit37 = "Radar";
	global.wikit38 = "An underground module equipped with a radar station. Surface access is provided via radio-lenses and a radio-transparent dome disguised as snow cover. One installation can track up to 150 km of surrounding airspace; more installations increase radar visibility range. Unfortunately, the inability to bring the antenna to the surface limits maximum visibility range and makes deploying more than three radars at once impractical. #Vulnerable to bombing: yes";
	global.wikit39 = "Infirmary";
	global.wikit40 = "A medical underground module equipped to the latest standards and intended to accelerate recovery of the wounded. Building more than one infirmary is impractical. #Vulnerable to bombing: no";
	global.wikit41 = "SAM Complex";
	global.wikit42 = "An underground module equipped with launch silos using converted AAM-LR ''Arrow'' missiles. It receives targeting from Radar and attacks a target if it tries to land troops near the base. Building the installation without Radar makes no sense. It does not attack the enemy on the world map if the base has not yet been detected. More installations increase air-defense reliability. #Vulnerable to bombing: yes";
	global.wikit43 = "''X-Tornado''";
	global.wikit44 = $"A fast multirole fighter intended for reconnaissance and interception of enemy aircraft. It was originally developed for special missions and rapid redeployment of a combat flight. Very fast. #Hull: {global.planedata[3, 1]} #Speed: {global.planedata[3, 6]} #Afterburner: {global.planedata[3, 7]} #Turn speed: {global.planedata[3, 8]} #Evasion: yes #Radar range: {global.planedata[3, 14]} #Acceleration: {global.planedata[3, 15]} #Max altitude: {global.planedata[3, 17]}";
	global.wikit45 = "XI-1 ''Wind''";
	global.wikit46 = $"A multirole fighter of Santa Claus's army, developed with Tails' involvement specifically to intercept robotic craft in Arctic conditions. It took part in many Arctic incidents. Equipped with a newest turbojet engine and specially shielded onboard systems. Currently somewhat outdated. #Hull: {global.planedata[1, 1]}  #Speed: {global.planedata[1, 6]} #Afterburner: {global.planedata[1, 7]} #Turn speed: {global.planedata[1, 8]} #Evasion: yes #Radar range: {global.planedata[1, 14]} #Acceleration: {global.planedata[1, 15]} #Max altitude: {global.planedata[1, 17]}";
	global.wikit47 = "XI-2 ''Penguin''";
	global.wikit48 = $"A deep modernization of the ''Wind'' fighter, created from a combination of the latest technologies and combat experience against robotic aircraft. Uses a pulse-detonation engine and an experimental radio-photon radar. Effective against most targets, but retains the flaws of a single-engine layout. #Hull: {global.planedata[2, 1]} #Speed: {global.planedata[2, 6]} #Afterburner: {global.planedata[2, 7]} #Turn speed: {global.planedata[2, 8]} #Evasion: yes #Radar range: {global.planedata[2, 14]} #Acceleration: {global.planedata[2, 15]} #Max altitude: {global.planedata[2, 17]}";
	global.wikit49 = "XI-3 ''Albatross''";
	global.wikit50 = $"A newest twin-engine multirole fighter combining the advantages of captured alloys with the benefits of a twin-engine layout. Pulse-detonation engines reinforced with captured alloys let the aircraft reach tremendous speed and carry a heavy combat load. Effective against any targets. #Hull: {global.planedata[4, 1]} #Speed: {global.planedata[4, 6]} #Afterburner: {global.planedata[4, 7]} #Turn speed: {global.planedata[4, 8]} #Evasion: yes #Radar range: {global.planedata[4, 14]} #Acceleration: {global.planedata[4, 15]} #Max altitude: {global.planedata[4, 17]}";
	global.wikit51 = "XI-4 ''Photon''";
	global.wikit52 = $"An advanced twin-engine robotic multirole fighter piloted remotely or in automatic mode. A light, strong superalloy body and twin-engine plant let the aircraft carry a combat load together with a powerful energy emitter, allowing effective attacks against air targets. The emitter is duplicated for defense against guided weapons. #Hull: {global.planedata[5, 1]} #Speed: {global.planedata[5, 6]} #Afterburner: {global.planedata[5, 7]} #Turn speed: {global.planedata[5, 8]} #Evasion: yes #Radar range: {global.planedata[5, 14]} #Acceleration: {global.planedata[5, 15]} #Max altitude: {global.planedata[5, 17]}";
	global.wikit53 = "XI-5 MiG-31AXE ''Polar Fox''";
	global.wikit54 = $"A heavy interceptor developed from the Soviet MiG-31 interceptor fighter and created specifically to use heavy ASM ''Avalanche'' missiles. It cannot conduct maneuvering close combat, but it can reach high speed and carry a heavy combat load over long distances, and also has a powerful radar for independent detection of air targets. #Hull: {global.planedata[6, 1]} #Speed: {global.planedata[6, 6]} #Afterburner: {global.planedata[6, 7]} #Turn speed: {global.planedata[6, 8]} #Evasion: no #Radar range: {global.planedata[6, 14]} #Acceleration: {global.planedata[6, 15]} #Max altitude: {global.planedata[6, 17]}";
	global.wikit55 = "XT-1 ''Scout''";
	global.wikit56 = $"A utility helicopter developed specifically for harsh Arctic conditions. Can carry up to 8 people, including cargo. Extremely vulnerable to enemy fighters; air cover is recommended. #Hull: {global.planedata[7, 1]} #Speed: {global.planedata[7, 6]} #Afterburner: {global.planedata[7, 7]} #Turn speed: {global.planedata[7, 8]} #Evasion: no #Radar range: {global.planedata[7, 14]} #Acceleration: {global.planedata[7, 15]} #Max altitude: {global.planedata[7, 17]}";
	global.wikit57 = "XT-2 VTOL ''Ranger''";
	global.wikit58 = $"A newest Vertical Takeoff and Landing Aircraft developed under Project X-MAS for high-speed transport in Arctic conditions. Can deliver up to 12 soldiers to the battlefield, including all cargo. Has an extremely familiar design. #Hull: {global.planedata[8, 1]} #Speed: {global.planedata[8, 6]} #Afterburner: {global.planedata[8, 7]} #Turn speed: {global.planedata[8, 8]} #Evasion: yes #Radar range: {global.planedata[8, 14]} #Acceleration: {global.planedata[8, 15]} #Max altitude: {global.planedata[8, 17]}";
	global.wikit59 = "XT-3 tiltrotor ''Whirlwind''";
	global.wikit60 = $"An advanced Project X-MAS tiltrotor capable of ultra-fast delivery of 20 soldiers to the battlefield. Has excellent lift capacity. #Hull: {global.planedata[9, 1]} #Speed: {global.planedata[9, 6]} #Afterburner: {global.planedata[9, 7]} #Turn speed: {global.planedata[9, 8]} #Evasion: yes #Radar range: {global.planedata[9, 14]} #Acceleration: {global.planedata[9, 15]} #Max altitude: {global.planedata[9, 17]}";
	global.wikit61 = "E-104 (Scout)";
	global.wikit62 = $"A scout robot of Eggman's Empire, equipped with an engine of unknown design that leaves no trail and does not consume fuel typical for turbojet aviation. The power system feeds the energy pulse emitters and, apparently, a plasma engine. The fuselage consists of a titanium frame covered with sheets of unknown alloy. The first aircraft detected by Project X-MAS. It precedes the appearance of more serious opponents and mainly performs reconnaissance. #Maximum detected speed: {global.eggplanedata[1, 7]} #Detected acceleration: {global.eggplanedata[1, 15]}";
	global.wikit63 = "E-140 (Fighter)";
	global.wikit64 = $"A standard robot-interceptor of Eggman's Empire. Fast and maneuverable, the fighter relies exclusively on its energy emitter. By default, it carries no guided weapons. Usually used to gain air superiority. #Maximum detected speed: {global.eggplanedata[2, 7]} #Detected acceleration: {global.eggplanedata[2, 15]}";
	global.wikit65 = "E-201 (Interceptor)";
	global.wikit66 = $"An elite robot-interceptor of Eggman's Empire. Capable of tremendous speed. Its armament consists of a twin energy emitter and guided weapons; in addition, it has defensive armament in the form of an emitter turret that destroys incoming guided missiles. Used either to gain air superiority or to protect important ships and facilities. #Maximum detected speed: {global.eggplanedata[3, 7]} #Detected acceleration: {global.eggplanedata[3, 15]}";
	global.wikit67 = "E-100 (Bomber)";
	global.wikit68 = $"A high-altitude bomber of Eggman's Empire with defensive armament, throwing plasma charges as bombs. Quite defenseless against fighters, but capable of shooting down fighters that risk entering close combat with it. #Maximum detected speed: {global.eggplanedata[4, 7]} #Detected acceleration: {global.eggplanedata[4, 15]}";
	global.wikit69 = "E-150 (CAS)";
	global.wikit70 = $"An Close Air Support plane of Eggman's Empire used to strike objects and support ground forces. Being small and nimble, the attacker has only a twin pulse emitter as armament. Although outwardly the attack aircraft looks vulnerable, in practice, thanks to its powerful weapons and armor, it is quite dangerous for many interceptors.#Maximum detected speed: {global.eggplanedata[5, 7]} #Detected acceleration: {global.eggplanedata[5, 15]}";
	global.wikit71 = "E-500 (Transport)";
	global.wikit72 = $"A standard transport of Eggman's Empire. Has defensive armament and is used to deliver robots to various combat operations and to transport cargo. Requires serious weaponry to destroy, since according to pilot reports, beam-plasma turrets are especially lethal and effective against missiles. ";
	global.wikit73 = "''Unrivaled'' (Mothership)";
	global.wikit74 = $"A huge mothership capable of reaching space and serving as Eggman's mobile base. Eggman himself is currently located aboard it. The ship has excellent protection and defensive armament, and is also always escorted by the Empire's best interceptors. Cannot be shot down by ordinary weapons easily. #Maximum detected speed: {global.eggplanedata[6, 7]} #Detected acceleration: {global.eggplanedata[6, 15]}";
	global.wikit75 = "Sonic Hedgehog";
	global.wikit76 = "Leader of the Project X-MAS squad: a blue spiky hedgehog, the fastest in his class. His high reaction speed gives him a 50% chance to avoid projectile hits, and his movement speed can create a sonic wave.";
	global.wikit77 = "Miles 'Tails' Prower";
	global.wikit78 = "Engineer of the Project X-MAS squad: a red-orange fluffy two-tailed fox, the fluffiest in his class. Somehow, he can fly and often uses it. Armed with a laser pistol powered by an emerald shard (making it unique) and a drone designed to distract the enemy on the battlefield.";
	global.wikit79 = "Amy Rose";
	global.wikit80 = "Machine gunner of the Project X-MAS squad, the pinkest in her class. Ruthless in combat, she uses a weighted sledgehammer and a high-rate multi-barrel machine gun. In a fit of rage she can turn into a whirlwind of hammer blows.";
	global.wikit81 = "Rouge Bat";
	global.wikit82 = "Saboteur of the Project X-MAS squad. Can fly and self-heal. Professional training gives her a 50% chance to parry melee strikes.";
	global.wikit83 = "Silver Hedgehog";
	global.wikit84 = "Technomage of the Project X-MAS squad. Wonderful equipment of unknown origin lets him paralyze and push enemies back in battle.";
	global.wikit85 = "Shadow Hedgehog";
	global.wikit86 = "Assaulter of the Project X-MAS squad. Ruthless and capable of destroying anyone in combat with his unknown weapon. Can teleport and create a shock field.";
	global.wikit87 = "Snow Conscript";
	global.wikit88 = "A snowman conscripted into Santa Claus's army. An ancient race that swore to defend the New Year holiday and Santa Claus himself if needed. The snowman population grows mainly through industrial sculpting and human snowman building. Only in the Arctic can snowmen be called up for military service. They possess all skills necessary for their tasks, from piloting to weapon handling and combined-arms combat.";
	global.wikit89 = "Knuckles Echidna";
	global.wikit90 = "Sapper of Project X-MAS. An excellent fighter capable of burrowing and moving underground, as well as laying mines in the field.";
	global.wikit91 = "Metal Sound";
	global.wikit92 = "A fast and agile close-combat robot often encountered in small Eggman raids. A turbojet engine at the design's center of mass allows course and landing-speed correction during airborne deployment. Despite protection made of strong alloys, vulnerable hinges and joints in the design do not provide proper protection against kinetic weapons.#Due to the complex design, the alloys used cannot be easily removed. #Armor - 10";
	global.wikit93 = "Pawn";
	global.wikit94 = "A heavy spherical robot with excellent protection against kinetic weapons. Unfortunately, the closed design and plating made of special alloys make the robot immune to most kinds of kinetic weapons. Fortunately, with difficulty, the robot can still be destroyed by our advanced large-caliber rifles. Capable of fighting at any distance thanks to ejectable harpoon hands and pulse energy emitters. #Since most of the alloys are in a regular spherical armor belt, the undamaged part can be easily removed. #Armor - 25";
	global.wikit95 = "UFO";
	global.wikit96 = "A disc-shaped levitating robot with excellent protection, immune to all forms of handheld kinetic weapons. The robot's levitation unit lets it hover above the surface and ignore terrain folds and elevation changes. Its armament is a powerful twin plasma pulse emitter whose charges produce a thermal explosion on impact. It also uses a compact reactor of unknown design as a power plant, which explodes when damaged, causing the usefulness of the debris to sharply decrease. An extremely dangerous opponent. #Armor - 40";
	global.wikit97 = "Turret";
	global.wikit98 = "An autonomous stationary defense turret with a plasma cannon apparently serves as the first defensive perimeter on Eggman's facilities and large ships. Its armor is strong enough to be impenetrable to small arms, but not enough to fully protect the turret from grenades and energy weapons.#Captured specimens gave some clarity about their design. As it turned out, the turrets are fully autonomous and do not rely on external power sources or communications. A complex optical-location station and a narrow directional friend-or-foe query node handle target selection and detection. If the presumed target gives an incorrect response or does not answer, the turret marks it as hostile. Recreating such a turret is too difficult for our technology level, but captured specimens can be restored and reflashed so that target-attack logic is inverted. However, due to heavy damage, the energy source cannot be restored, nor can the gun; therefore our version's armament will be replaced with a beam cannon, and power will be supplied directly from the base. #These turrets are extremely dangerous, but ineffective on complex terrain. Use cover and throw grenades at them from outside their reach!#Armor - 40";
	global.wikit99 = "Emitter";
	global.wikit100 = "As it turned out, Eggman uses plasma weapons of various configurations and power as his main long-range weapons. The most common model of his energy emitter is built on superconductors and is an ordinary linear magnetic accelerator using a magnetic field to hold and direct plasma. The general firing principle resembles a railgun, while the plasma itself is formed in the emitter by a powerful electric discharge from a gas mixture obtained from atmospheric air without using separate ammunition. Requires a fairly powerful energy source.#Because we cannot capture an intact specimen, we cannot recreate a fully working model, since the plasma we form is unstable and cannot fly farther than a few dozen meters without breaking apart. Nevertheless, based on this emitter, we can try to create our own beam weapon using a different operating principle";
	global.wikit101 = "Superalloy";
	global.wikit102 = "A unique composite material not seen before, created using electromagnetic and powder metallurgy. The ''superalloy'' is based on high-alloy steel. This steel is then reinforced with a carbon-based composite with a thin metal-ceramic layer similar in properties to pobedit. Structural integrity is achieved through a thin cobalt-based binding shell and complex heat treatment. Surprisingly thin composite sheets have moderate flexibility, allowing them to be shaped into complex forms.#Unfortunately, we cannot recreate this composite even under laboratory conditions, but we can use wreckage, since even thick, seemingly monolithic composites turned out to be armor packages made of thin sheets joined by diffusion welding";
	global.wikit103 = "Moto-Bug";
	global.wikit104 = "A small robot made of fairly common alloys and packed with explosives. Dangerous only at short range, where it detonates itself. Fortunately, useless in conditions with sharp elevation changes.";
	global.wikit105 = "HQ";
	global.wikit106 = "An underground command complex that supports the command staff and makes their work in Project X-MAS convenient. Module equipment includes command and support staff workstations, as well as a holographic map of the Arctic Pole displaying all known targets. #Vulnerable to bombing: no";
	global.wikit107 = "Eggman's Transmission Encryption";
	global.wikit108 = "Eggman's radio transmissions themselves are not that hard to intercept, and project agents periodically manage to detect them on the airwaves, allowing nearby enemy presence to be found even without radar station coverage. However, the contents of these transmissions could not be understood for a long time.#As it turned out, Eggman uses quantum cryptography and a complex repeater network. Such a system is unbreakable at our current level of technological development, if only because secretly listening to the communication channel is impossible. Fortunately, a loophole was found: none of Eggman's ships or robots communicates with the center directly. Thus, by reflashing a captured repeater (previously removed from a captured Eggman transport ship), we can receive outgoing information from any ship and thereby learn, for example, its type.#Nevertheless, full information about the ship's activity is unfortunately impossible to obtain, since commands from the center are transmitted by address and will never reach the receiver of an already shot-down or written-off ship...";
	global.wikit109 = "Modular Buildings";
	global.wikit110 = "Arctic conditions make construction expensive and difficult. Because of permafrost, even creating a foundation becomes difficult: as heat loss from the building warms the ground, ice and frozen soil lose bearing capacity, making the building unstable. A proven modular-construction technology allowed us to build small autonomous stations that expand the project's operating area within acceptable time and cost. In addition, we managed to create small modular production complexes that will allow more toys to be made for the New Year, which will increase project funding";
	global.wikit111 = "Onboard Emerald Detector";
	global.wikit112 = "Although many Mobian technologies are inapplicable on Earth, it turned out that with a number of tricks, adapting the Chaos Emerald detector to Earth conditions is not difficult. While electromagnetic disturbances created by a Chaos Emerald are not easy to detect from high altitude under Earth conditions, it was found that a radar-reflected radio signal receives strong interference caused by such a source, expressed as instability in the Doppler pattern.#Normally the radar filter cuts off such disturbances as ordinary interference caused by complex terrain, but in the updated configuration, when certain patterns match (which nevertheless cannot be detected instantly), the radar reports the presence of a Chaos Emerald nearby";
	global.wikit113 = "AAM-LR R-03 ''Zealot''";
	global.wikit114 = "Since the start of the project, we have increasingly faced the enemy aviation's numerical superiority. Since there is no reason to believe that this superiority can be nullified later, we must look for other ways to counter the enemy. The Long-Range Air-to-Air Missile ''Zealot'' proved a successful example of such a method: created from the AAM-MR ''Stingray'' and using the solid-fuel motor from the AAM-LR ''Arrow'', this missile uses a high-explosive warhead and a nose section with detachable optically guided micromissiles with rod warheads. Thanks to this, the missile is most effective against dense enemy air groups at long range, since while attacking the main target it launches micromissiles at neighboring hostile targets.#Unfortunately, the missile is expensive, uses semi-active guidance, and cannot attack aircraft not near the target with micromissiles due to weak engines; its heavy weight also prevents hanging more than two missiles per hardpoint#Range - 200";
	global.wikit115 = "Improved Aircraft Cannon";
	global.wikit116 = "The aircraft-cannon model used by Project X-MAS has a high rate of fire and is powerful enough to damage all known Eggman aircraft. However, as it turned out, using aircraft cannons is extremely difficult because any Eggman weapon outranges them. Fortunately, captured materials can partially offset this flaw while keeping the same dimensions by increasing pressure in the powder chamber and barrels, giving the shells higher velocity and therefore increasing damage and effective range. However, due to increased recoil, the rate of fire had to be reduced to avoid stalling the aircraft during continuous fire#Range - 50";
	global.wikit117 = "Improved Detection Methods";
	global.wikit118 = "From the very start of the project, we faced difficulty detecting Eggman's aviation. Despite taking radar portraits, the frequency of ship detection did not increase, since even ships of the same model did not match. Finally, the reason was found: as we discovered while studying many wrecks of different ship classes, Eggman uses a complex system of dynamic radio-lenses that constantly change the aircraft's radar profile to the most advantageous one at the current moment, not necessarily the stealthiest. Thus, Eggman prevented characteristic radar portraits from being identified while also complicating detection by disguising the radar profile as the nearest object reflecting radio waves, whether another aircraft or a dense thundercloud mass.#Having found this pattern, we cannot fully nullify this technology, but the target detection speed will definitely improve thanks to an adaptive reflected-signal filter";
	global.wikit119 = "Eggman's Robotics";
	global.wikit120 = "After studying many robot wrecks, initial optimism about finding a solution to all problems quickly vanished: it became clear that we can hardly even recreate one of these machines, let alone disable them preventively via a vulnerability. Eggman's robotics are highly autonomous and rugged. Despite sometimes bizarre designs, each robot's architecture is well thought out. Besides well-protected and reliable servomotors, each robot has a powerful optical-location station with all-aspect visibility, explaining the robots' keen sight and observation.#The main problem turned out to be the surprising fact that despite high autonomy, the robot does not have powerful computing capacity for making complex decisions and precisely processing all information. Apparently, we are mostly dealing with an interface that relies heavily on a centralized server. Obviously, this rational solution has a number of shortcomings, but it also prevents enemies like us from copying the technology. Nevertheless, perhaps this is our chance: if we can detect and destroy such a center, perhaps we can win this war...";
	global.wikit121 = "Final Solution to the Problem";
	global.wikit122 = "It seems we have finally found a way out of the current stalemate. As it turned out, our initial guesses were correct: all Eggman robotics rely on a centralized server that is expectedly located on the mothership. By itself this information has little value, since we still could not detect that ship, but now we do not need to. Since we still have not found more than 4 emeralds, it is obvious that the other 3 are most likely part of Eggman's ship power plant. He has often used similar solutions before, so the hypothesis is likely correct. Thanks to this, we can use the Chaos Emeralds' ability to resonate over long distances and assemble a resonating reactor from three emeralds, provoking a cascade overload of the power grids and potentially a further explosive ejection of the emeralds far apart from one another. Building such a reactor in a reasonable time is possible only at our base, but fortunately it will not take much space and will not endanger the base itself if all safety measures are followed, since our base is fortified and located underground.#This should lead to the mothership's destruction or crash, but we can be sure Eggman will quickly detect such a reactor by its characteristic disturbances and their source, and therefore attack our base with everything he has, including the mothership. Thus, the reactor should not be built until we are ready for the final battle...";
	global.wikit123 = "Beam Energy Weapon";
	global.wikit124 = "The initial assessment proved correct: our own beam energy weapon can indeed be developed from the emitter. First, clarification is needed: this is NOT another photon laser. A classic laser is extremely inefficient in atmospheric conditions, has a power ceiling due to the beam heating atmospheric air into plasma, and quickly scatters with distance. The alternative was a pulsed infrared beam weapon, made possible by using the captured emitter. Like an ordinary laser, it emits a visible light stream due to a short powerful pulse creating visible supercontinuum glow, but it is not subject to such strict limitations and transfers energy more effectively.#Since this is not a kinetic weapon, it will destroy armor through thermal shock, and armored opponents will no longer be such a serious problem as before, but the high cost and low rate of fire may prevent mass rearmament of all fighters with it";
	global.wikit125 = "Chaos Resonator";
	global.wikit126 = "An experimental Chaos Emerald resonator designed to overload the power grid of Eggman's mothership. Build it to initiate the final battle, but be ready for it! #Vulnerable to bombing: yes";
