	global.wikit140 = "";
	global.wikit141 = "Basics: Base Construction";
	global.wikit142 = "Project X-MAS has resources to build only one base. Due to the small size of the operation area, building other full bases has been deemed impractical. By default, the base location is unknown to the enemy, since the base is hidden from external observation and uses a distributed radio-repeater network. Nevertheless, the enemy can discover the base by flying over it. Plan the base wisely, since in case of bombing, modules neighboring the attacked module (especially hangars) can be damaged.#Project X-MAS funding and results are summed up every week.";
	global.wikit143 = "Basics: Project X-MAS";
	global.wikit144 = "Project X-MAS is part of Santa Claus's army as a separate autonomous army and reports directly to Santa Claus.#Project funding depends directly on its effectiveness, since as Santa Claus's facilities are destroyed, his ability to support you decreases. The project's task is to prevent Dr. Eggman's activity at the North Pole. Try to keep an optimal number of scientists and engineers at the base so you can complete the projects you need in time without overspending the budget";
	global.wikit145 = "Basics: Aviation Maintenance and Use";
	global.wikit146 = "Aviation is the main force of Project X-MAS. The number of aircraft can be increased by building more hangars and ordering more aircraft. Each aircraft's equipment can be changed in the ''Details'' window on the ''Aviation'' tab. Each aircraft can also be renamed in this window by pressing the button with the aircraft name. Each aircraft undergoes refueling, rearming, and repair as needed, and these processes cannot be stopped immediately. Choose aircraft weapons wisely, since they cannot be changed instantly. If your aircraft lack range, replace them with newer models or use external fuel tanks";
	global.wikit147 = "Basics: World Map";
	global.wikit148 = "The world map shows the North Pole operation region with important points of interest for the project, such as major enterprises and settlements belonging to Santa Claus. Besides them, the map displays detected enemy forces and reports of enemy activity, if any. Detected enemy squadrons can be intercepted with the ''Intercept'' button in the menu or in the UFO information window after they are detected. In addition, on the world map you can view messages and speed up time.#Cover the territory with radars and air-defense systems to detect and passively destroy the enemy, and suppress enemy attempts to destroy or bomb important objects";
	global.wikit149 = "Basics: Surface Construction";
	global.wikit150 = "After Modular Buildings are developed, separate buildings can be constructed on the world map using the ''Build'' button on the world map. Building factories can increase funding over time, radars increase radar coverage, and air-defense systems attack detected enemy squadrons.#Keep in mind that air defense can attack only targets detected by radars, and any objects on the map can be attacked by enemy aviation. Therefore, all important objects must be covered by air-defense systems and radars, especially if your aviation is numerically inferior to the enemy";
	global.wikit151 = "Basics: Soldiers";
	global.wikit152 = "Project X-MAS soldiers consist of unique heroes (such as Sonic) and Santa Claus's regular army. Regular infantry is not strong, but quickly gains experience, can use different weapons and throw grenades, and these soldiers can also be quickly replaced. Unique heroes are less universal and cannot be replaced if they die.#If soldiers are wounded in battle, they will receive treatment at the base and cannot be used until they recover. Soldier equipment can be changed in the ''Details'' window on the ''Infantry'' tab. Each soldier can also be renamed. Killed soldiers are located on the ''Memorial'' tab.#Always keep a ready garrison at the base in case the enemy decides to attack you!";
	global.wikit153 = "Basics: Ground Combat";
	global.wikit154 = "Ground combat is long and dynamic. First (if absent) a player-controlled soldier is deployed, and his presence is mandatory: if he dies, combat will not continue until a replacement is deployed. Any other soldiers can be deployed as allies, but they will not behave as effectively. Super abilities are used with ALT and CTRL, F1 is healing and F2 is grenade throw (requires a regular soldier on the battlefield). Jump with Space, move with WASD. Melee combat is F, dash is Shift.#If a mission is especially difficult but must be completed, and the number of enemies on the mission is limited, try launching a preliminary air strike on the target.";
	global.wikit155 = "Basics: Interaction with Santa Claus's Army";
	global.wikit156 = "Project X-MAS does not wage war alone, but as part of Santa Claus's army, which independently fights to save the New Year. You may not see all allied operations, but the ally will support you where possible. In addition, some of your technological developments can be used by the ally if enough resources are available, which is an extra incentive to minimize enemy activity in the theater of operations. Most often the ally will help during attacks on its own objects, but it can also independently intercept enemy squadrons";
	global.wikit157 = "Basics: Air Combat";
	global.wikit158 = "Air combat is fast and complex. Assess your forces correctly: if you see that the forces are unequal, it is better to strike and retreat or leave the battle immediately, since losing an expensive aircraft may be an unaffordable luxury. If you are confident in victory or losses do not scare you, you can skip air combat by pressing ''Auto battle'' and calculating its results automatically; otherwise, you will have to fight manually. Choose aircraft armament correctly: bombers can be dangerous in close combat but are easily shot down by long-range missiles, while short-range missiles and aircraft cannons can be most effective against fighters.#Watch your transport: if the enemy shoots it down during interception, you will lose not only the transport but also the infantry it carries!";

	
